snippet.textDisplay:
Everyone seems to think just because KD and Kyrie are friends they're going to be able to play together.

I don't think they're going to mesh together at all!

Kyrie has arrogance syndrome!

In his mind, he's better than everyone else and "He Thinks Everyone Else Feels The Same Way He Does, And His Teammates, Past And Present, DON'T"!

How do you make public proclamations like that, and your team plays BETTER Without You?

I don't see him and KD playing well together at all, and truthfully Brooklyn's guards were tight enough! They didn't even need Kyrie!

KD, DJ, those additions would have been enough without Kyrie.

I don't want to go so far as to say Kyrie's toxic, but his ATTITUDE is!

He's another Star who wants us to stay out of the locker room, but yet your always the one running your mouth, an in effect giving the media something to pounce on by publicly criticizing your own team, it's players and needs!

So what makes y'all think he's going to listen to KD?

Y'all all saw how he played in Boston, him trying to lead. Where did that get him?

TRADED!

Now he's doing the same thing there in Brooklyn! He doesn't have a right to speak forth coming like he has, because he hasn't established, or it hasn't been established that he's actually a good fit for them there!

Kyrie is a "Lloyd World Be Free" of the 2000's!

Us OG's know and remember the talent that he had!

One on One skills that were pure Elite, but never won anything! Was never a good fit anywhere!

Was all world, "In His Own Mind", which took away his respect and admiration that players once had for him...

For those that don't remember, he and Kyrie, two of a kind.....

snippet.textDisplay:
As a Bucks fan who watches most of the games It's so nice to finally have a team that has a chance to get to the finals. But hard sometimes knowing that while they have a very deep bench The Bucks need a starting player that will give you 20-25 points every game with 50% FG avg. that can defend and also go odd and score 35 when the rest of the team (mainly Giannis) is struggling. Middleton and Bledose are so close to being that but disappear one to many games. It's fine for the Regular season but hurts the team in the Post season when teams try even harder to shut down the Freak. I also get the type of player isn't as common as you would think with having to play a Robin role and would cost a good amount of salary cap and mean that we would prolly lose 2 solid bench players and maybe a starter , but again the team is so deep they can afford it. The biggest mistake they made for team building from last year to this year was giving Bledose his contract. He is a good player but i would have love to seen The Bucks use him to trade up or free up salary cap to go get and upgrade.


It may seem like i'm being over critical when talking about an overall very good team that hasn't been a team that can have a chance to win a title that hasn't been anywhere close to the since "Big Dog" and Ray Allen days in Late 90's very early 2000's but I know Giannis wants to win bad and likes playing for Milwaukee and i fear will leave the team if they cant at least get the finals this year or have enough hope for the next 2-3 years to keep him here. If The Bucks lose him , i will have a hard time watching the Bucks who have felt like a team that you go to get good enough to be a starter on a legit title contender or at the very least a role player on said type of team. That's what the Bucks have been for almost the past 20 years. I know that makes me a fair weather fan but when you only get a HoF player every 20 years and they leave early enough in there careers to be key parts of other teams title runs , it's just hard to watch a team be a an 8th seed that gets knocked out first round at best.


I will watch Giannis where ever he goes and not be bitter about him not staying on the team because i know he just wants to win and you can't be a hater for that since i feel like the Bucks will have failed him for not giving him enough of help.
